Chatham House, the Royal Institute of International Affairs, is a world leading independent policy institute based in London. As a global think tank, our mission is to help build a sustainably secure, prosperous and just world.

We have an opportunity for a CRM Administrator who will join our Digital team. The role holder will be responsible for first line support of the development and maintenance of Chatham House's CRM and its key interfaces. This includes solving problems at source where possible, escalating issues to the CRM team or our partner supplier where appropriate. You will be working within a team of three, supporting colleagues across the institute. This is a hybrid role where there is flexibility to split your working week between home and the office.

We are an equal opportunity employer, we value diversity and do not discriminate on the basis of protected characteristics. We encourage applications from all backgrounds. If there is anything we can do to improve your experience or support you, please get in touch with HR@Chathamhouse.org.


Main Responsibilities


Undertake day-to-day maintenance, development and support of the Institute's database (MS Dynamics 365) to ensure it performs to optimal level and in line with users' expectations;
Monitor and troubleshoot data and systems-related problems that may arise such as financial transactions, event registration, membership applications due to data or issues in 3rd party integrations;
Work collaboratively with colleagues and external suppliers to define and implement additional functionality, test workflows and troubleshoot technical problems and issues ensuring that they are accurately documented and understood;
Process data briefs from users providing them with appropriate segmented data;
Import data from spreadsheets and text files ensuring its's cleaned and QA'd as part of process;
Support CRM team members in the querying, analysis and presentation of supporter data across the organisation;
Continue to improve the quality of the data within the CRM;
Encourage best practice and user adoption of the CRM.


Requirements

Training will be provided where needed with opportunities for continued professional development.

Essential

You will have/are:


Experience of working with MS Dynamics 365;
Experience of querying data, working with Views, Marketing Lists;
Ability to customise Forms, Views and Entities;
Experience working with security roles and assigning access;
Experience with data mapping and imports;
Proficient in manipulating data in Excel;
Broad experience of working across the MS stack;
Broad knowledge of data protection, GDPR (and privacy) legislation and best practice and an appreciation of how it is applied in an organisation;
Good communication (verbal and written) skills;
Strong organisation and time management skills;
The ability to build effective working relationships with a wide range of users and stakeholders;
Self-starter able to use own initiative and to prioritise effectively;
Strong troubleshooting and problem resolution skills.


Desirable


Experience of deploying through dev, testing, production environments;
Working with Solutions and deploying Customizations;
Experience of using SQL or other languages to extract and manipulate database information;
Experience creating workflows;
Experience with Power Platform, including Power Automate and Power Bi;
Interest in international affairs.


Benefits

Benefits include approximately 37 days annual leave (inclusive of public holidays and Chatham House closure days), pension salary exchange, employee assistance programme, parental leave, flexible working and other benefits designed to suit your own personal lifestyle. All of this, in a professional, engaging and intellectually stimulating environment.

